<br>
1. Damage per cast (the possible &quot;crit&quot; number maximum)<br>
2. Damage/Mana efficiency<br>
3. Spell cast/recast rate<br>
<br>
Spell resist is too random to include, even though we have a weak -10 to the resist on our spells.<br>
<br>
When balancing <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> any</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> other class' nukes to ours, it should not exceed ours in any of the 3 components.<br>
<br>
<br>
If you consider an encounter that ONLY takes cold-based damage, and using 1 DD spell during the battle....<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Druid:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Level 65 with 4000 mana<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Wizard:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Level 65 with 4000 mana<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Before Battle:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Druid casts Xanuusus' Blessing on his/her group (20 hp/tick heal)<br>
Druid casts Shield of Bracken on his/her group (40 damage shield)<br>
Druid casts Protection of Seasons on his/her group<br>
Druid casts Spirit of Eagle on his/her group<br>
Druid casts Blessing of the Nine on his/her group (32 AC, 618 HP, 8 mana/tick)<br>
<br>
Wizard casts Spellshield on each group member for a cost of 6 peridots.<br>
<br>
Druid and Wizard meditate to full<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Battle Begins:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Druid chains Winter's Frost 10 times, with 200 mana left = 13950 damage / 3800 mana / 92 seconds<br>
<br>
Wizard chains Draught of Ec'i 18 times, with 40 mana left = 14400 damage / 3960 mana / 72 seconds (includes 1 second spell gem refresh)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Results:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Druid:</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
--Damage = 13950 + Damage Shield (40 per hit) = 14550 if the DS only hits <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> once per tick</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
--Healing = 15 ticks * 20 hp * 6 players = 1800 hp<br>
--Resists = +72 to fire and cold<br>
--Debuff = -55 to cold on the MOB and -24 to AC on MOB if the druid uses his/her extra mana to cast E'ci's Frosty Breath at the beginning of the fight.<br>
--Buff = 32 AC, 618 HP, 8 mana/tick + SoE...<br>
------Damage Per Second = 158<br>
------Damage Per Mana = 3.82 (not counting pre-fight mana use)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Wizard:</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
--Damage = 14400<br>
--Healing = (800 - 61<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  * 6 = 1092 (ONLY if AE battle)<br>
--Resists = NONE<br>
--Debuff = <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> MAYBE</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> -8 to fire and cold (if not overwritten)<br>
--Buff = NONE<br>
------Damage Per Second = 156 (for duration of fight)<br>
------Damage Per Mana = 3.63<br>
<br>
<br>
In a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> purely nuking</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> analysis, the numbers become this:<br>
<br>
Druid = 13950 DD / 151 DPS / 3.67 DPM<br>
<br>
Wizard = 14400 DD / 200 DPS / 3.63 DPM<br>
<br>
<br>
Total DD damage leaves the wizard +450<br>
Total DPS leaves the wizard +49 (although he twiddles his thumbs OOM for 20 seconds)<br>
Total DPM leaves the wizard <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> -0.04</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Maybe you can accept the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> extremely weak</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> 3% damage increase wizards have over druids, but what about when you consider <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> all the other stuff they are doing WHILE doing their DD</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->??? <p><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=59003"><img src="http://home.nc.rr.com/jelong/newsig.gif"></a><br><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif></font></center></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukeryiawinterwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Keryia Winterwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/11/02 10:35 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cold Damage for wizards not up to par</span><hr size=1> One thing we can't calcuate is the affect of resistance.  The resist adjust for the druid spell is 0 for the wizard -50.  If I understand that properly wizard spells will hit more often for more damage then the druid one.<br>
