<br>
Now to compound the problem, Druids have a 800 dmg rain for 500 mana to compare to our 750 dmg for 400 mana.   This will allow the druid to further outstrip wizards in the DPS department in cold using the standard nuke while &quot;rain&quot; techniques we have used for so long.<br>
<br>
Here is the post I left in the Ice Flame post in &quot;General&quot; <br>
-----------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
I agree here. The nukes between in &quot;any&quot; form of ice, fire, or magic should not be close between a wizard and druid.<br>
<br>
The DPS and efficiency should not be close, let alone have the druid ahead of the wizard.<br>
<br>
This illustrates an oversight of Verant that SHOULD be handled before any release of PoP. And NO -- I don't consider &quot;ancient&quot; spells when doing this balance because of the relative rarity of these.<br>
<br>
Ways to handle this should be:<br>
1) Add a Faster castering Wizard &quot;big&quot; nuke. Should be roughly 2.1K (Garrison like) dmg with 350 - 400 or so DPS. Spell availability should be like druid Moonfire btw.<br>
<br>
2) Big revamp of Ice Spear. Increase the dmg slightly but slash the recast time massively.<br>
<br>
3) Or *cough - nerf* the druid spell to be substantially less than Ice spear. I am not an advocate of nerfing but Verant does not seem to have any desire to &quot;add&quot; to wizard capabilities (takes them away).<br>
<br>
Justification? Ports have lost value and druids also port along a &quot;much better TL&quot; being given to magicians. That leaves us with ONLY nukes. And now we don't even have clear unchallenged nuke superiority against FR/MR mobs (likely most of the plane of fire and such)?????<br>
<br>
AvgWiz -- lvl 60 sorceror  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukolensl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kolen SL</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/14/02 2:51 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Big Cold nuke needs to be added</span><hr size=1> Few points...<br>
<br>
Damage shield damage doesn't stack. Only one druid (or in a raid more likely the mage) will &quot;get&quot; the dps from that.<br>
<br>
You're ignoring crits, which will adjust the figures further.<br>
<br>
In sustained damage situation (ie almost any raid target from velious onwards) wizards have better mana regen through harvest and flappy.<br>
<br>
Druids are also, I believe one of the few casting classes without a viable click nuke (we have some, but they're OD only, and generally pretty weak except one for finishing off quads).<br>
<br>
As for the PoP spells... I'll see about the rain. I know our current rains suck on resists, and generally you don't come out ahead. Remember wizard nukes are (supposed to be at least) harder to resist than other classes. No one is terribly excited about their PoP nukes. Last I looked half our new nukes were downgrades from Moonfire, and it seems similar for most classes (though i'll admit there are now some nice druid spells on test for PoP, so I'm not overly fussed personally)<br>
<br>
Figure those in and come back with the figures <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
-Kolen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uavgwiz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AvgWiz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/14/02 6:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Big Cold nuke needs to be added</span><hr size=1> But if a Druid adds in DoTs into the mix, the DPS balance gets even more slanted toward the druid.   And there are many, many free DoT providing click effects compared to Rend Robe (which does not drop any more) and the much weaker Conflag robe.<br>
<br>
Regarding your rains &quot;sucking on resists&quot; -- newsflash -- wiz rains are worse.   In fact, your Winter Storm has a resist adjust of -50 compared to Tears of Marr -10.   On top of that, you get debuffs which the wizards really don't get barring the staff of tflux (-9 cr/fr) which stacks with nothing.<br>
<br>
So in effect, the druid DPS exceeds wizard DPS in the cold arena now in nuke, rains, and also AoE.<br>
<br>
Once again I state, either the wizard DPS in these arenas need a very, very substantial increase or the druid DPS in these areas need a substantial decrease.  But remember this, I believe mages should be outnuking druids especially with these changes, so they can either rebalance both wiz or mages OR just balance druids downwards.<br>
<br>
AvgWiz -- lvl 60 sorceror <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukolensl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kolen SL</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/14/02 9:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Big Cold nuke needs to be added</span><hr size=1> Disclaimer: I'm assuming raid situations here.. 90% of my playtime is raids so for me that's the important venue. I realise that isn't the case for everyone though.<br>
<br>
As it stands currently... There is a bit of umm'ing and ahh'ing as to if our non-free dots are better than moonfire for efficiency (specialisation plays a role in that) so <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  at the moment</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> dots are largely a non-issue. <br>
<br>
We don't currently have a cold debuff, though that will change in PoP, and the benifit isn't limited to druids <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
The dps from free dots is ... feeble. Drones of Doom (most common) is 6dps if you're feeling generous with rounding. Wrath of Nature is a whopping 9dps. There also can be possible slot limitations on mobs if you have a number of shaman/necros on the raid. The &quot;weak&quot; conflag robe is a steady 41dps or so (higher with crits, not sure if ID works on items?). I agree rend robe isn't really realistic these days <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
I can't comment on spells that aren't live yet, the new rain may well be worth casting, we'll see.On resists I note you're completely ignoring the casting level buff wizards get, completely seperate from the spell data. I admit I haven't paid a lot of attention there, so am willing to be told I'm wrong, but I assume that is also used in resist calculation.<br>
<br>
I also see you haven't addressed the crit issues, which is effectively a boost across all nukes, especially with the available of SCFM and the new planar SCF (I don't think druids get this at the moment, though they're still playing around it seems). Nor the mana regen issue. There's also the issue of aggro, since priest classes do not have access to SCS nor any kind of aggro reducing spells.<br>
<br>
As an aside I remember doing back of envelope sustainable dps calculations for a druid and that conflag robe dps is about where druids are at for sustainable dps assuming SCM3, SCF3, focus items, raid buffs, and moonfire. Not exactly awe inspiring to say the least. <br>
<br>
I have no compunctions in saying I don't think mages should out nuke druids. Pets add more than enough to compensate for the difference, and the solution there is to fix remaining pet woes, though I guess that probably falls into the &quot;too hard&quot; category for Verant. :/<br>
<br>
I guess my point is that looking at damage potential purely by looking at spell data can be misleading. There are other significant factors that come into play, especially when considering sustainable output which is important right now (and may not be in PoP). Also don't downplay the available of clicky nukes, even the conflag robe is non-trivial damage (effectively what, 625dmg for 50-60mana?).<br>
