New Damage/Second = 165.0000 (Old = 77.6471)<br>
<br>
(I only used +10% of the Iceflame E'ci, because anyone can use a +20% focus item, which may not stack with Iceflame of E'ci)<br>
<br>
Now, I do understand that I am comparing a level 65 druid nuke to a level 60 wizard nuke, but give that some <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> serious</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> thought.  Wizards have <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> no</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> healing ability, and <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> none</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> of the additional abilities of druids.  Even <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> with</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> our <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> LEVEL 64</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> buff spell, our <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> BEST</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> cold nuke only exceeds the druid one by 8.6% in DPS and 19% in efficiency.  Also remember that your DoTs still blow our DD efficiency away.<br>
<br>
I welcome your (constructive) criticism.  Please show me anything unreasonable in this suggestion.<br>
<br>
Before you bring up the resist issue, think about exactly how big of a deal -10 to a resist <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> really</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> is.  The randomness of resists is so unpredictable that even <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> LURES</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (-300 to resist) are <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> fully</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> resisted many times.<br>
<br>
I also ask that you not include any AA skills in the comparison, as I have not included any in mine.  A <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> base configuration</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> druid should be balanced with a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> base configuration</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> wizard.  (This includes <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> only</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> level-based experience, and no gear) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukolensl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kolen SL</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/14/02 6:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kolen</span><hr size=1> Heh, this will teach me for browsing other class forums while bored at work <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Forgive the unstructured replies, still waking up here.<br>
<br>
I tend to disagree on items, items have always been a part of class balance. What you can equip (cloth/leather/chain/plate) is a fundamental part of a class, and that extends to what you can <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> do</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> with items now. You can't just pretend those capabilities don't exist.<br>
<br>
Aazlar: I think my guild has more free copies of SS at the moment than Moonfire, and at least on Trib I've seen moonfire at the Bazaar all of twice. YMMV. If we're not talking Ice Spear, or chain casting, a barebones wizard will outdamage a bare druid with moonfire, if nothing else from innate crits. This is at 60, current day. I'll admit that's not much though. The trouble is when you DO include AA's and clicky nukes the cap widens dramatically (factor of 2-3 for sustained dps). So yes, unfortunately wizards depend on AA's and items to maintain their lead in damage output. :-/<br>
<br>
Ignore dots. Druid current dots are within a hairs breadth of an evoc spec moonfire cast (Umm. Breath of Ro may edge it out since it's also evoc, but it doesn't stack because of a debuff comopnent). Our PoP upgrade is just faster, not more efficient (as it stands I believe beastlords end up better at dotters than we do, bleh). Maybe relevant for the alter spec druids (we seem split about 50/50, although my guild is more like 90% evoc..), but I know of no Conjure spec druids offhand <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Basically I just can't see how you can realistically ignore AA's and items. Luclin level spells (such as moonfire) will have been balanced on the availability of items and AA's. In this case druids do not have SCFM, which is a significant boost to long term efficiency. Aside from that I'd suggest a ISS clone with the shorter recast at 62-63 instead of tweaking ISS. On the druid spell, I'm largely indifferent to the change you suggest, either way <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Although Verants intent with Planes of Power nukes seems to be bigger nukes, less (or not terribly improved) efficiency, so not sure how important the bigger guns really will be.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I think we disagree on some basic points to be considered when looking at these things, but this isn't my forum and will bow out <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  It's been a pleasant discussion though, somewhat refreshing to discuss class capabilities without frothing at the mouth (yeah, so sue me, I read EQClerics in my odd masochistic moments.. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
